# Build Inbound v1

## Step

Chartered at full strength per Joel ("we want inbound too … no sense
fucking around") — built in parallel with outbound, not gated on its
proof. Resolved when the dispatcher's inbound surface (operator
messages, commands, interactions) runs on Chat SDK handlers behind
contract v2 in **shadow**: receiving live traffic alongside the
existing gateway path, receipts compared, self-originated-message
rejection verified (the self-wake-loop defense is non-negotiable),
without acting on anything the old path also acts on (no double
execution — shadow observes, journals, and proves parity).

The **cutover** — the new path becomes the acting dispatcher and the
hand-rolled channels start dying — is NOT this step. It stops for Joel
with shadow receipts on the table.
